    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Injured person evaluated at facility by contract safety representative",
      "Injured person transported by helicopter to shore base in Patterson, Louisiana",
      "Injured person taken to Occupational Medicine Clinic in New Iberia, Louisiana",
      "Injured person placed on restricted duty by CETCO"
    ],
    "summary": "On December 12, 2014, a CETCO Plug and Abandon crew was rigging up Coiled Tubing equipment on Ankor's Ship Shoal 229 A facility. While using a lift boat's crane to lift a riser section with nylon slings held by studded bolts, one of the sling eyes parted and struck a crew member on the right wrist, causing a broken wrist. The incident was caused by inadequate training, improper lifting equipment selection, lack of pre-use inspection, poor supervision, and inadequate procedures and job safety analysis.",
